        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Defer closed menu rebuilds during refresh",
        "body": "## Summary\nPrepare attached closed menus after refresh work settles, and keep stale nonempty menu content on open while store or token refreshes are active.\n\n## Validation\n- `swift test --filter StatusMenuOpenRefreshTests`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Runtime Proof\nPushed cleanup fix at `c39cb661`, then added debug-only redacted lifecycle logs at `998f1a07` to prove the real app path without exposing menu text or account data.\n\nFocused menu-refresh proof run:\n\n```text\n$ swift test --filter StatusMenuOpenRefreshTests\nTest \"closed attached menu is prepared before next open after invalidation\" passed\nTest \"closed attached menu preparation waits for store refresh to finish\" passed\nTest \"closed attached menu preparation waits for token refresh to finish\" passed\nTest \"closed menu rebuild cleanup runs when weak menu disappears\" passed\nTest \"menu open keeps stale nonempty content while store refresh is active\" passed\nTest \"menu open keeps stale nonempty content while token refresh is active\" passed\nTest run with 25 tests in 1 suite passed\n```\n\nLive app proof from a freshly packaged debug build at `/Users/alec/Dev/CodexBar/CodexBar.app`, driven through macOS Accessibility on June 1, 2026 PDT:\n\n```text\n[2026-06-01T07:05:41.696Z] [DEBUG] com.steipete.codexbar.app: menu open kept existing content during refresh items=13 provider=claude storeRefreshing=1\n[2026-06-01T07:05:43.290Z] [DEBUG] com.steipete.codexbar.app: closed menu rebuild completed items=17 provider=claude\n```\n\nInterpretation: while a refresh was active, opening the stale nonempty menu kept the existing 13 items instead of rebuilding synchronously; after the menu was closed and refresh work settled, the closed-menu rebuild path populated the next version with 17 items. The proof is redacted to lifecycle state, item counts, provider id, and refresh state only.\n\nAlso ran `git diff --check`; it passed with no output.\n",
